cs.DC, cs.PF, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on scheduling MapReduce jobs, which is a distributed computing paradigm. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is also likely as the paper aims to minimize the total weighted completion time of the jobs, which is a performance metric. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper considers power-aware scheduling, which involves controlling the energy consumption of the system. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper proposes algorithms for solving the scheduling problem. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses convex programming, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning.
